    dc:title "A new species of Hyphessobrycon Durbin (Characiformes: Characidae) from the middle rio São Francisco and upper and middle rio Tocantins basins, Brazil, with comments on its biogeographic history" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4639084>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4639076>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4639086>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4639080>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4639082> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4639084>
    dc:description "Fig. 4. Fin lengths as function of standard length by sex in males (black square, n = 20) and females (white circle, n = 14) of Hyphessobrycon diastatos, (a) dorsal fin, and (b) anal fin." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4639084/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4639076>
    dc:description "Fig. 1. Hyphessobrycon diastatos, all from Brazil, Bahia, São Desidério, rio Galheirão (or rio da Estiva), affluent of rio Grande, rio São Francisco basin, (a) holotype, MZUSP 114030, 24.4 mm SL, male, (b) paratype, MZUSP 114029, 25.2 mm SL, male, and (c) paratype, MZUSP 114029, 20.8 mm SL, female." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4639076/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4639086>
    dc:description "Fig. 6. Adipose fin variation in Hyphessobrycon diastatos, paratypes, all from MZUSP 114029, (a) 20.1 mm SL, (b) 19.4 mm SL, and (c) 18.1 mm SL. Arrows indicate the position of the adipose fin." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4639086/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4639080>
    dc:description "Fig. 3. Live coloration of Hyphessobrycon diastatos. (a) paratype, MZUSP 114029, 25.2 mm SL, male, Brazil, Bahia, São Desidério, rio Grande drainage, rio São Francisco basin, and (b) paratype, MZUSP114031, 26.7 mm SL, female, first anal-fin rays broken, Brazil, Goiás, São Domingos, rio São Domingos, rio Tocantins basin." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4639080/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4639082>
    dc:description "Fig. 5. Distribution of Hyphessobrycon diastatos in the middle rio São Francisco basin and upper and middle rio Tocantins basin, Brazil. Yellow dot represents the holotype and red dots the paratypes. Each dot may represent more than one collection event." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4639082/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

